Note the `_` syntax (e.g. `findByUser_UserId`) — that's Spring Data's way of reaching through a relationship: "find by the `user` field's `userId` property." It only works because the field name in your entity (`user`, `guest`, `roomType`, etc.) matches exactly. Same naming-must-match rule as `mappedBy`.

